						<summary>

						<p>This much damaged inscription is dated <hi rend="bold">[Chāḷukya] Vikrama year 27, Chitra[bhānu],</hi> the other details being lost.<note n="243-1">In the list of <hi rend="italic">B.K.</hi> inscriptions appended to the <hi rend="italic">Annual Report on South Indian Epigraphy,</hi> 1928-29, this inscription has been wrongly assigned to the reign of Jagadēkamalladēva.</note>The date corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1102-03.</hi></p>						

